How to make module TagMeCab.pm work
------------------------------------

note: MeCab and its Perl wrapper, which this modul uses is not on 	CPAN, so you need to install them manually

Install MeCab:
---
 % wget http://mecab.googlecode.com/files/mecab-0.996.tar.gz
 % tar zxfv mecab-X.X.tar.gz
 % cd mecab-X.X
 % ./configure 
 % make
 % make check
 % su
 % make install
---


Install Ipadic Dictionary:
---
 % wget http://mecab.googlecode.com/files/mecab-ipadic-2.7.0-20070801.tar.gz
 % tar zxfv mecab-ipadic-2.7.0-XXXX.tar.gz
 % mecab-ipadic-2.7.0-XXXX
 % ./configure
 % make
 % su
 % make install
---


MeCab Perl wrapper:
---
 % wget http://mecab.googlecode.com/files/mecab-perl-0.996.tar.gz
 % tar xfv mecab-perl-X.XX.tar.gz
 % cd mecab-perl-X.XX
 % perl ./Makefile.PL
 % make
 % su
 % make install
---

Run test.pl, if there is error:
Can't load '/home/wishmaster/mecab-perl-0.996/blib/arch/auto/MeCab/MeCab.so' for module MeCab: libmecab.so.2: cannot open shared object file: No such file or directory at /usr/lib64/perl5/DynaLoader.pm line 190.
you need to set links for mecab libraries:
---
 % ldconfig -p | grep mecab   # should print empty output
 % cat /etc/ld.so.conf        # should print "include ld.so.conf.d/*.conf"
 % su
 % echo "/usr/local/lib" > /etc/ld.so.conf.d/mecab.conf   # we add link to mecab libraries
 % ldconfig
 % ldconfig -p | grep mecab   # should now print something like this:
	
	libmecab.so.2 (libc6,x86-64) => /usr/local/lib/libmecab.so.2
	libmecab.so (libc6,x86-64) => /usr/local/lib/libmecab.so

 # run "perl test.pl" to see, if everything's ok
---

 


mess up with location of mecab.pm (so Treex can find it)

